{"id":56864,"title":"The \"leicester lasso\" lateral canthoplasty.","abstract":"To describe an innovative technique of lateral canthal tendon (LCT) anchoring to the lateral orbital rim on its inner aspect using a \"lasso\" technique, in order to provide the ideal vector.A retrospective case review of seven patients (n = 7), performed from 2009 to 2013 at our institution by the senior author (RGS).Excellent results in all cases with optimal restoration of form and function.The 'Leicester Lasso' technique is a safer technique of securing the LCT to the orbital rim.","date":"2014-03-11","categories":"Eye Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24614550","annotations":[{"name":"Leicester","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leicester"},{"name":"Lasso","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lasso"},{"name":"Landing craft tank","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landing_craft_tank"},{"name":"Canthus","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canthus"},{"name":"Euclidean vector","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_vector"},{"name":"Mathematical optimization","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_optimization"},{"name":"Institution","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Institution"},{"name":"Author","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Author"},{"name":"Grammatical aspect","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammatical_aspect"},{"name":"Orbit","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orbit"},{"name":"Ideal (ring theory)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ideal_(ring_theory)"},{"name":"2013","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013"},{"name":"Order (